    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="73"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Adams</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1728.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 31, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I thank you for your very interesting despatch of
                    the 15th of March, No. 1167. I have read with deep interest the debates which
                    have occurred in Parliament on the subject of the newly proposed reform bill.
                    Whatever difficulty that measure may encounter in Great Britain, it is manifest
                    that it will have the benefit, whatever the weight may be, of a moral opinion
                    throughout the world.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams, Esq., <hi rend="italic"
                                >&amp;</hi>
                        </hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">c., &amp;c. &amp;c.</hi>,</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
